body:
The API and the supervisor are moving towards a more multi-app compatible format for the target state (and away from database dependent ids). This PR introduces support for the new target state for the supervisor (see below for the new target state format).

This is large change as the supervisor needs add support for the new state format on the GET request, as well as on `apps.json`, modifying everywhere in the code that used to rely on the old format (e.g. validations, contracts, migrations,etc. ) In addition to that it adds some conversions from the old target state format into the new target state format for backwards compatibility on the supervisor API. The change also adds support for the new target state format on target state PATCH. Finally it performs some refactoring on most of the places where `appIds` where used.

This is a MAJOR change, as installing this new supervisor version, will restart all the currently running services as metadata inside the services needs to change (the restart still waits for users to lift the lock though).

```typescript
export type StateV3 = {
	[uuid: string]: {
		name: string;
		parent_device?: string;
		config?: {
			[varName: string]: string;
		};
		apps: {
			[uuid: string]: {
				/**
				 * @deprecated to be removed in state v4
				 */
				id: number;
				name: string;
				class: 'fleet' | 'block' | 'app';
				parent_app?: string;
				is_host?: boolean;
				releases?: {
					[uuid: string]: {
						/**
						 * @deprecated to be removed in state v4
						 */
						id: number;
						services?: {
							[name: string]: {
								/**
								 * @deprecated to be removed in state v4
								 */
								id: number;
								/**
								 * @deprecated to be removed in state v4
								 */
								image_id: number;
								image: string;
								/**
								 * Defaults to true if undefined
								 */
								running?: boolean;
								environment: {
									[varName: string]: string;
								};
								labels: {
									[labelName: string]: string;
								};
								contract?: AnyObject;
								composition?: ServiceComposition;
							};
						};
						volumes?: AnyObject;
						networks?: AnyObject;
					};
				};
			};
		};
	};
};
```
